
Company: Axiom Space

As of: Thu Mar  4 04:02:07 AM EST 2021

Ex-NASA employees and entrepreneurs -- plans to have first 
commercial space station.

Plans to have haitable module to attach to ISS by mid-2020s.
NASA contract for $140 million awarded in 2020.

Plans to attach multiple modules to ISS, which will detach 
and become an independent space station when ISS is retired.

Plans to send first commercial crew to ISS in January 2022.


They hope to do 'a couple of flights per year'.

Currently 110 employees, hope to reach 1000 in 2024


